<p>As the Stripe docs mentioned, we can only reactivate a subscription that has <em>not</em>
been fully canceled. If today is <em>beyond</em> the period end, then the user will need
to create an entirely new subscription. That's why we only show the button in our
template during this period.</p>
<p>But just in case, add an "if" statement: <code>if !$user-&gt;hasActiveSubscription()</code>,
then we'll throw a new exception with the text:</p>
<blockquote><p>Subscriptions can only be reactivated if the subscription has not actually ended.</p>
</blockquote>
